# OpenAI Codex Mapping Playbook

Copy this folder into the root of a project where Codex will help configure Caracal Console provider and resource fields.

This setup mirrors the Claude Code and GitHub Copilot mapping playbooks. It helps Codex translate provider dashboard labels into visible Caracal Console fields, verify mappings with docs, and keep secrets masked.

## Use

1. Copy `AGENTS.md` and `.codex/` into your project root.
2. Configure Codex to read `AGENTS.md` and `.codex/config.toml`.
3. Ask for a focused workflow such as provider mapping, resource mapping, configuration review, or provider onboarding.

## Contents

- `AGENTS.md`: primary operating guide.
- `.codex/AGENTS.md`: short pointer for Codex setups that read nested agent guidance.
- `.codex/console-fields.ground-truth.json`: single Console field ground truth.
- `.codex/agents/`: specialist mapping agents.
- `.codex/skills/`: reusable mapping and safety skills.
- `.codex/config.toml`: MCP, documentation, approval, and safe operation guidance.

Do not paste raw provider secrets into chat. Use redacted values or environment variable names.
